{"id": "kvh1665702777986", "title": "Stored Procedures on PostgreSQL", "breadcrumbs": ["DBMS Support", "Database Connectors", "PostgreSQL", "Stored Procedures on PostgreSQL"], "url": "https://docs.rocketsoftware.com/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kvh1665702777986.html", "html": "<html><body><header class=\"zDocsTopicPageHead\"><h1 class=\"css-g931ng\">Stored Procedures on PostgreSQL</h1><div class=\"zDocsTopicActions\" role=\"list\"><div class=\"zDocsBundlePagination\" data-testid=\"next-prev-container\" role=\"listitem\"><div class=\"zDocsPrevTopicButton zDocsPrevTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Previous:   SQL Support for PostgreSQL \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Previous:   SQL Support for PostgreSQL \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nzp1665702776275.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-prev\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-prev\"></use></svg></a></span></div><div class=\"zDocsNextTopicButton zDocsNextTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Next:   Service Stored Procedures on PostgreSQL \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Next:   Service Stored Procedures on PostgreSQL \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lqs1665702778056.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></a></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsMyDocsMenu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Add to My Topics\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Add to My Topics\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" id=\"addToMyDocsDropdownTrigger\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg>Add to My Topics</span><div aria-labelledby=\"pdfDropdown\" class=\"dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right\"><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/kvh1665702777986.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub\">Add selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/kvh1665702777986.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub_head\">Add Topic &amp; Subtopics with topic head</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/kvh1665702777986.html?finish_action=mydocs_pub\">Add entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsWatchButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Watch\" class=\"d-lg-flex d-none zDocsSubscribeButton\" data-tooltip-content=\"Watch\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsSubscribeButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye zDocsSubscribeButton\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsSubscribeButton\">Watch</span></span></div><div class=\"zDocsExportPdfMenu zDocsExportMenu\" data-testid=\"export-pdf-menu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Download PDF\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Download PDF\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529386\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529386\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kvh1665702777986.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kvh1665702777986.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kvh1665702777986.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kvh1665702777986\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Stored Procedures on PostgreSQL\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__stored_procedures_on_postgresql_170702\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Whenever possible or desirable, the connector generates stored procedures for most basic I/O operations. A stored procedure encapsulates one or more SQL statements and is stored in compiled format. During execution, the parsing phase can be skipped.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__p_d58004e1_d58005e1_d58006e1\">The stored procedure name used for execution by Uniface is derived from the schema name and the operation name:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__table_d5282e1_d5283e1_d5284e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Component Name and Operation Name Specification</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__table_d5282e1_d5283e1_d5284e1__entry__1\">\n Procedure name\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__table_d5282e1_d5283e1_d5284e1__entry__2\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kvh1665702777986__table_d5282e1_d5283e1_d5284e1__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">TableName</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">_FET</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kvh1665702777986__table_d5282e1_d5283e1_d5284e1__entry__2\">\n Fetch the record specified by the primary key\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kvh1665702777986__table_d5282e1_d5283e1_d5284e1__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">TableName</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">_FET_FORUPDATE</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kvh1665702777986__table_d5282e1_d5283e1_d5284e1__entry__2\">\n Lock the record when the record is being modified\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kvh1665702777986__table_d5282e1_d5283e1_d5284e1__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">TableName</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">_DEL</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kvh1665702777986__table_d5282e1_d5283e1_d5284e1__entry__2\">\n Delete the record specified by the primary key\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kvh1665702777986__table_d5282e1_d5283e1_d5284e1__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">TableName</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">_INS</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kvh1665702777986__table_d5282e1_d5283e1_d5284e1__entry__2\">\n Insert a record\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kvh1665702777986__table_d5282e1_d5283e1_d5284e1__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">TableName</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">_UPD</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kvh1665702777986__table_d5282e1_d5283e1_d5284e1__entry__2\">\n Update the record specified by the primary key\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__topic_d38382e1_d38383e1_d38384e1_d38385e1_d38386e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d422293e149\">\n                       \n Creating Stored Procedures\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__p_d58010e1_d58011e1_d58012e1\">Stored procedures can be created if the procedures connector option is <code class=\"ph codeph\">on</code>. They are created either on-the-fly if the table is not yet present in the DBMS, or by the scripts generated by the Create Table facility. If created on the fly, the connector does not function correctly if the procedures option is on and there are no procedures present in the DBMS.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__note_w3691ab1b5b7b5_w3692ab1b5b7_w3693ab1b5_w3694ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The default server delivered by PostgreSQL binaries supports a maximum of\n            100 arguments for stored procedures. If you are using the default server, and have\n            tables with more than 100 fields, the PGS connector cannot create stored procedures for\n            them. In this case, you must disable the use of stored procedures by setting the\n            procedures option to <code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code>.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__topic_d38387e1_d38388e1_d38389e1_d38390e1_d38391e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d422293e167\">\n                       \n Stored Procedure Parameters\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__p_d58016e1_d58017e1_d58018e1\">Parameters are defined for stored procedures when the stored procedure is created. The following definitions are made:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__li_d26303e1_d26304e1_d26305e1\">Parameters to use\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__li_d26306e1_d26307e1_d26308e1\">Data types of each parameter\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__li_d26309e1_d26310e1_d26311e1\">SQL statement\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__li_d26312e1_d26313e1_d26314e1\">Position of the parameters in the SQL statement\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__p_d58019e1_d58020e1_d58021e1\">Parameters for field lists used in <code class=\"ph codeph\">insert</code> are:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">@insert1, @insert2, ..., @insert<var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var></code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__p_d58022e1_d58023e1_d58024e1\">Parameters for field lists used in <code class=\"ph codeph\">update</code> are:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">@update1, @update2, ..., @update<var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var></code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__p_d58025e1_d58026e1_d58027e1\">Parameters for field lists used in <code class=\"ph codeph\">delete</code> are:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">@delete1, @delete2, ..., @delete<var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var></code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__p_d58028e1_d58029e1_d58030e1\">Parameters for <code class=\"ph codeph\">where</code> clauses in <code class=\"ph codeph\">fetch</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">delete</code>, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">update</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">@where1, @where2, ..., @where<var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var></code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__p_d58031e1_d58032e1_d58033e1\">The parameter that specifies the inclusion of the U_VERSION field in the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">where</span> clause is <code class=\"ph codeph\">@uversion</code>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__topic_d38392e1_d38393e1_d38394e1_d38395e1_d38396e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d422293e256\">\n                       \n Segmented Fields\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kvh1665702777986__p_d58037e1_d58038e1_d58039e1\">If the automatic field list includes segmented fields (packing codes SC or SU), stored procedures are not used, even if enabled. Instead SQL is used to retrieve all the data except the segmented field data.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529386\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529386\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Stored Procedures on PostgreSQL Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Stored Procedures on PostgreSQL Whenever possible or desirable, the connector generates stored procedures for most basic I/O operations. A stored procedure encapsulates one or more SQL statements and is stored in compiled format. During execution, the parsing phase can be skipped. The stored procedure name used for execution by Uniface is derived from the schema name and the operation name: Table 1. Component Name and Operation Name Specification Procedure name Meaning TableName _FET Fetch the record specified by the primary key TableName _FET_FORUPDATE Lock the record when the record is being modified TableName _DEL Delete the record specified by the primary key TableName _INS Insert a record TableName _UPD Update the record specified by the primary key Creating Stored Procedures Stored procedures can be created if the procedures connector option is on . They are created either on-the-fly if the table is not yet present in the DBMS, or by the scripts generated by the Create Table facility. If created on the fly, the connector does not function correctly if the procedures option is on and there are no procedures present in the DBMS. Note: The default server delivered by PostgreSQL binaries supports a maximum of 100 arguments for stored procedures. If you are using the default server, and have tables with more than 100 fields, the PGS connector cannot create stored procedures for them. In this case, you must disable the use of stored procedures by setting the procedures option to off . Stored Procedure Parameters Parameters are defined for stored procedures when the stored procedure is created. The following definitions are made: Parameters to use Data types of each parameter SQL statement Position of the parameters in the SQL statement Parameters for field lists used in insert are: @insert1, @insert2, ..., @insert n Copy Parameters for field lists used in update are: @update1, @update2, ..., @update n Copy Parameters for field lists used in delete are: @delete1, @delete2, ..., @delete n Copy Parameters for where clauses in fetch , delete , and update : @where1, @where2, ..., @where n Copy The parameter that specifies the inclusion of the U_VERSION field in the where clause is @uversion . Segmented Fields If the automatic field list includes segmented fields (packing codes SC or SU), stored procedures are not used, even if enabled. Instead SQL is used to retrieve all the data except the segmented field data. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}